<br>
SoT actually passed on their CT patch day, so we (NB) went into fear and cleared CT and then went and killed Vind / Statue as that was also ours as per the rotation.<br>
<br>
The point im trying to make is, if you got rotation commitments you should do them first if possible and then go off and do the other stuff you got planned, if you dont want to do your rotation commitments first then simply pass on them to the next guild, if you happen to end up one day with like 4 mobs from rotation that you need to kill but you also wanted to go to X Zone for some reason, then simply pass on the mob to the next Guild in rotation. Seems simple enuff to me, that way everyone benefits, you dont have to race around like a headless chicken trying to kill stuff in the 24hr timeframe. <p><p><a href="http://www.noble-blade.net"><imgsrc="http://http://www.eqforge.com/profiles/10395.jpg"><br>
